  "title": "Electrostatics - sign of work_pot_ energy change",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows positively charged Particle X, a horizontal distance d from positively charged Particle Y.\" src=\"/images/e69eb94154b68dd6d5010bc5a7d8002a.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Charged Particle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> is fixed in place. A second positively charged Particle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span> with the same magnitude of charge is moved from very far away to a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\"><math alttext=\"d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>d</mi></math></span></span> from Particle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span>, as shown in the figure. Which of the following claims about the work done on Particle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span> is correct?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i1",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">An external force does positive work on Particle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span>, increasing the electric potential energy of the two-particle system.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">An external force does positive work on Particle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span>, decreasing the electric potential energy of the two-particle system.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The field does positive work on Particle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>Y</mtext></math></span></span>, increasing the electric potential energy of the two-particle system.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The field does negative work on Particle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span>, decreasing the electric potential energy of the two-particle system.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
